cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SY 

This paper focuses on designing and implementing a network coding-enabled reliability architecture for next generation wireless networks, specifically using WiMAX platforms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of packet erasure codes, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different mechanisms for reliability, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for cross-layer designs, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
